	<article>

		<header>
			
			<h1>Growing role of Southern Africa in ACP/LDC sugar exports </h1>

			
			<h4>
												23 June 2013
										</h4>

					</header>


		
		
					<p>The US Department of Agriculture (USDA), in its annual report on sugar in Swaziland published in April 2013, has projected a 4% increase in sugar cane production in Swaziland in marketing year (MY) 2013/14, reaching 5.9 million tonnes, on the basis of “an increase in the area planted”. Sugar production could potentially reach 725,000 tonnes, up 6% compared to the 2012/13 season, following an increase in sucrose content.</p><p>Exports are projected to increase to 350,000 tonnes in MY 2013/14, up 6% on MY 2012/13, which was itself 5% higher than in 2011/12. Exports are largely to the EU, although in 2013/14 the tariff-rate quota (TRQ) for the US market could well be taken up.</p><p><b>Swaziland sugar production and marketing 2011/12–2013/14 (tonnes)</b></p><table class="renderedtable" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0">
<tr>
<td width="154" valign="top">  &nbsp;
  </td><td width="154" valign="top">  2011/12
